232
00:09:42.582 --> 00:09:43.764
Yes. Ma. you're a star.

233
00:09:43.800 --> 00:09:45.917
- There's only one Cookie Lyon.
- Damn right.

234
00:09:45.953 --> 00:09:49.203
- Thank God for that.
- Oh. look at Miss Teri Sunshine.

235
00:09:49.238 --> 00:09:50.833
Where you get
all that spunk from. girl?

236
00:09:50.857 --> 00:09:52.435
You better be careful
'fore I throw

237
00:09:52.459 --> 00:09:53.786
them big-ass cankles
out my house.

238
00:09:53.810 --> 00:09:55.927
Oh. no. no. no.
I love your cankles. baby.

239
00:09:55.963 --> 00:09:57.462
- Oh...
- Mm. they're not too big.

240
00:09:57.497 --> 00:09:59.914
- They're too big.
- No. they're not too big.

241
00:10:00.968 --> 00:10:02.161
<i>COOKIE:
Girl. what the hell</i>

242
00:10:02.185 --> 00:10:03.501
are you wearing?

243
00:10:03.536 --> 00:10:05.804
Um... Jamal and I
used to wear these

244
00:10:05.839 --> 00:10:07.650
to our sleepovers
all the time. so...

245
00:10:07.674 --> 00:10:09.757
No wonder that boy
ran off to London.

246
00:10:09.792 --> 00:10:12.643
I thought he was running away
from Lyon drama.

247
00:10:12.679 --> 00:10:14.495
I really miss him.

248
00:10:14.530 --> 00:10:16.397
COOKIE:
Please don't get me started.

249
00:10:16.433 --> 00:10:18.015
I miss him so much.

250
00:10:18.051 --> 00:10:21.336
Anyway. why do we need
to have this slumber party?

251
00:10:21.371 --> 00:10:24.772
Okay. I need some advice.

252
00:10:24.807 --> 00:10:26.202
- Mm-kay.
- Okay. so Giselle and I

253
00:10:26.226 --> 00:10:29.243
have a really big meeting
tomorrow.

254
00:10:29.278 --> 00:10:31.446
Like. big. "Big" as in "huge."

255
00:10:31.481 --> 00:10:33.364
I'd tell you who it is.

256
00:10:33.399 --> 00:10:35.700
but I can't. so I won't.

257
00:10:35.736 --> 00:10:37.702
But I really. really need

258
00:10:37.737 --> 00:10:39.687
to nail the pitch. okay?

259
00:10:39.722 --> 00:10:41.789
- We really got to land her.
- Oh.

260
00:10:41.825 --> 00:10:43.040
So it's a her.

261
00:10:43.076 --> 00:10:44.525
Of course it's a her.

262
00:10:44.560 --> 00:10:47.028
Our label is about women.

263
00:10:47.063 --> 00:10:49.196
for women. by women.
featuring women.

264
00:10:49.232 --> 00:10:50.649
women. women. women.

265
00:10:50.684 --> 00:10:53.518
Oh. honey. that's a lot
of weave and tampons.

266
00:10:53.553 --> 00:10:54.502
It's half the budget.

267
00:10:54.537 --> 00:10:55.832
- Yeah.
- (laughing)

268
00:10:55.856 --> 00:10:57.205
Well. y'all go right on ahead

269
00:10:57.240 --> 00:10:58.773
with your vajayjay power.

270
00:10:58.808 --> 00:11:00.792
(groans)
The only thing is.

271
00:11:00.827 --> 00:11:03.394
Giselle will not sign anyone

272
00:11:03.429 --> 00:11:05.964
before we get
our marquee artist. so...

273
00:11:05.999 --> 00:11:08.666
I mean. doesn't Giselle
understand that it is your job

274
00:11:08.701 --> 00:11:11.002
to go out. find the artists
and turn them into stars?

275
00:11:11.038 --> 00:11:12.748
I mean. that's what
good labels do.

276
00:11:12.772 --> 00:11:15.807
Oh. look at you. You miss it?

277
00:11:15.842 --> 00:11:17.392
What?

278
00:11:17.427 --> 00:11:19.827
This. Empire. the music.

279
00:11:19.862 --> 00:11:21.796
This used to be in your blood.

280
00:11:21.831 --> 00:11:25.150
I need something new.
something fresh.

281
00:11:25.185 --> 00:11:26.534
Like your talk show.

282
00:11:26.569 --> 00:11:30.188
And my community center.
among other things.

283
00:11:30.223 --> 00:11:32.590
Uh. this is time for me.

284
00:11:32.625 --> 00:11:35.009
Okay? I'm building my own brand.

285
00:11:35.062 --> 00:11:36.822
Oh. you about to be
a whole mogul out here.

286
00:11:36.846 --> 00:11:39.680
Yes. It is Cookie's time.

287
00:11:39.715 --> 00:11:42.116
Ooh. I almost forgot.

288
00:11:45.372 --> 00:11:47.939
- Potato chips?
- Yes. girl. salt and sweet.

289
00:11:47.974 --> 00:11:49.924
Isn't that Lucious' thing?

290
00:11:49.959 --> 00:11:51.209
So?

291
00:11:53.279 --> 00:11:55.613
So. you miss him.

292
00:11:55.649 --> 00:11:58.282
Look how mad you just got.

293
00:11:58.318 --> 00:11:59.411
- You miss him.
- I didn't get mad.

294
00:11:59.435 --> 00:12:01.219
- No. you<i> miss</i> miss him.
- (sighs)

295
00:12:01.254 --> 00:12:02.965
Do you think you guys are gonna
get back together?

296
00:12:02.989 --> 00:12:04.583
Girl. do I look like
a damn fortune tell...

297
00:12:04.607 --> 00:12:06.341
Look. uh. Becky?

298
00:12:06.376 --> 00:12:09.243
Eat this ice cream 'fore
I put your ass out my house.

299
00:12:09.278 --> 00:12:11.557
-(clicks tongue)
I thought we were sharing.
-Ah-ah. Please. just...

300
00:12:11.581 --> 00:12:12.908
- The... A quiet moment. please.
- I thought we were girlfriends.

301
00:12:12.932 --> 00:12:14.281
J-Just eat-eat the ice cream.

302
00:12:14.317 --> 00:12:16.384
♪ <i>Five. four. three</i> ♪

303
00:12:16.419 --> 00:12:18.369
♪ <i>Two. one. leggo. level up</i> ♪

304
00:12:18.404 --> 00:12:20.805
♪ <i>Level up. level up.</i>
<i>level up. level up...</i> ♪

305
00:12:20.841 --> 00:12:23.052
BECKY:
And we just want you to know
that we will be dedicating

306
00:12:23.076 --> 00:12:24.803
all of our time
and attention to you

307
00:12:24.827 --> 00:12:26.761
as if you are our only artist.

308
00:12:26.796 --> 00:12:28.929
Ain't that what I'd be. though?

309
00:12:28.965 --> 00:12:32.133
Well. actually. you would be
treated like our first artist.

310
00:12:32.168 --> 00:12:33.968
- Ah.
- I mean. we have a vision

311
00:12:34.003 --> 00:12:35.732
for your career
that nobody else has.

312
00:12:35.756 --> 00:12:38.623
My experience in brand
marketing. Becky in A&R...

313
00:12:38.658 --> 00:12:39.907
That's a killer combination.

314
00:12:39.942 --> 00:12:41.542
Yes. you're big.

315
00:12:41.578 --> 00:12:45.163
but we can make you even bigger
on multiple platforms.

316
00:12:45.198 --> 00:12:46.781
Yeah. I...

317
00:12:46.816 --> 00:12:49.250
Listen. I really like
and admire the both of you.

318
00:12:49.285 --> 00:12:51.136
so I'm-a be honest with y'all.

319
00:12:51.171 --> 00:12:52.120
- Thank you.
- I appreciate that.

320
00:12:52.155 --> 00:12:53.671
I'm not signing with Bossy.

321
00:12:53.706 --> 00:12:56.307
Y'all too small.
But I'll tell you what I can do.

322
00:12:56.343 --> 00:12:58.959
I'll let y'all leak to<i> TMI</i>
that we had this meeting.

323
00:12:58.995 --> 00:13:00.590
That should help
y'all out a little bit.

324
00:13:00.614 --> 00:13:02.847
- So generous of you.
- Thank you for that.

325
00:13:02.882 --> 00:13:05.316
These some
nice-ass offices. though.

326
00:13:05.352 --> 00:13:07.952
Hit me up with
your designer's info. okay?

327
00:13:07.987 --> 00:13:09.637
- Okay.
- (laughs softly) Be well.

328
00:13:09.672 --> 00:13:11.506
(whispers):
Bye. now.

329
00:13:11.541 --> 00:13:13.941
(elevator bell dings)

330
00:13:13.976 --> 00:13:15.505
"Treat you like
the only artist"?

331
00:13:15.529 --> 00:13:17.490
Why did it sound so good
in my head last night?

332
00:13:17.514 --> 00:13:19.647
- Were you high last night?
- No. I wasn't high...

333
00:13:19.682 --> 00:13:21.682
Yeah. but just a little bit.

334
00:13:21.718 --> 00:13:23.701
(footsteps approaching)

335
00:13:23.736 --> 00:13:26.015
MAYA:
Andre. security brought
this gentleman up.

336
00:13:26.039 --> 00:13:27.266
He says that
you're expecting him.

337
00:13:27.290 --> 00:13:29.223
but he's not on my calendar.

338
00:13:31.144 --> 00:13:32.293
Mouse.

339
00:13:32.328 --> 00:13:33.722
Oh. no. no.
He's good. he's good.

340
00:13:33.746 --> 00:13:35.547
Maya. close that door. please.

341
00:13:37.233 --> 00:13:39.934
- (both laugh)
- When the hell
did you get out. boy?

342
00:13:39.969 --> 00:13:41.769
Hey. why didn't you call me?

343
00:13:41.805 --> 00:13:43.399
I tried to hit you up. I think
you must've changed your number.

344
00:13:43.423 --> 00:13:45.168
-Ah.
-I been here about an hour.
They wouldn't let me up.

345
00:13:45.192 --> 00:13:46.552
Oh. I'm sorry
about that. man. Listen.

346
00:13:46.576 --> 00:13:48.492
I am stoked to see you.
Have a seat.

347
00:13:48.528 --> 00:13:50.206
I'm-a pour you something
to drink. man. What do you like?

348
00:13:50.230 --> 00:13:53.731
Shoot. everything. No ice.

349
00:13:53.766 --> 00:13:56.684
- So. what you got planned. man?
- Frankly. uh. I could use a job.

350
00:13:56.719 --> 00:13:59.687
You know how it is.
Or maybe you don't.

351
00:13:59.722 --> 00:14:01.139
Maybe I don't?

352
00:14:01.174 --> 00:14:02.807
(laughs)
You playing. boy.

353
00:14:02.842 --> 00:14:04.169
- You know I know.
- (clears throat)

354
00:14:04.193 --> 00:14:07.295
And I can help you out.

355
00:14:07.330 --> 00:14:08.490
What type of job
you looking for?

356
00:14:08.514 --> 00:14:10.348
All right.
(clears throat)

357
00:14:10.383 --> 00:14:12.511
- I've been thinking about this
for a long time.
- All right.

358
00:14:12.535 --> 00:14:14.313
I want something
where I can wear a suit.

359
00:14:14.337 --> 00:14:15.731
- Oh. yeah. Oh. yeah.
- I've always dreamed

360
00:14:15.755 --> 00:14:17.988
of having an office
with a window.

361
00:14:18.024 --> 00:14:20.859
Maybe something here at Empire?

362
00:14:20.894 --> 00:14:22.555
Close to yours.
so we can hang. huh?

363
00:14:22.579 --> 00:14:24.189
See. that's what
I'm talking about.

364
00:14:24.213 --> 00:14:26.242
Let me go down there.
check out. see what's open.

365
00:14:26.266 --> 00:14:28.243
But first step is gonna have to
be. you know. you go to HR...

366
00:14:28.267 --> 00:14:31.752
Can't you just do me a solid?
I mean. you came out to this.

367
00:14:31.788 --> 00:14:33.070
I came out to nothing...

368
00:14:34.857 --> 00:14:37.625
after staying in because of you.

369
00:14:40.580 --> 00:14:42.880
Damn right you owe me.

370
00:14:45.201 --> 00:14:47.168
I know I owe you.

371
00:14:47.203 --> 00:14:49.003
And I'm-a square you up. okay?

372
00:14:49.038 --> 00:14:52.106
Might take a day or two.
You got my word.

373
00:14:52.142 --> 00:14:53.769
-Just like in the day. right?
All right.
-Yeah. man.

374
00:14:53.793 --> 00:14:54.942
I got you.

375
00:14:57.380 --> 00:14:59.613
I'd like to thank you all
for getting behind me

376
00:14:59.649 --> 00:15:02.350
while my father's on sabbatical.
and for stepping up

377
00:15:02.385 --> 00:15:04.351
in light of some
recent staff departures.

378
00:15:04.387 --> 00:15:06.532
Are you gonna be announcing
promotions to fill those slots?

379
00:15:06.556 --> 00:15:08.038
Absolutely. Very soon.

380
00:15:08.074 --> 00:15:09.456
Thank you very much. Porsha.

381
00:15:09.492 --> 00:15:11.276
We got some big announcements
this week.

382
00:15:11.311 --> 00:15:13.744
Empire will provide the
theme song for Fox Basketball...

383
00:15:14.930 --> 00:15:16.631
and Charlie Dupree

384
00:15:16.666 --> 00:15:18.482
- will star as Lucious Lyon...
- All right.

385
00:15:18.518 --> 00:15:21.286
In the new Empire film.

386
00:15:23.089 --> 00:15:25.205
Thank you.

387
00:15:25.241 --> 00:15:28.325
Thank you.
Thank you. Thank you.

388
00:15:28.361 --> 00:15:29.610
(slow clap)

389
00:15:35.302 --> 00:15:36.918
Hey. Andre.

390
00:15:40.373 --> 00:15:42.907
Maybe you should make
an announcement about me?

391
00:15:42.942 --> 00:15:44.625
Tracy? Um...

392
00:15:44.660 --> 00:15:46.010
What are you doing here?

393
00:15:46.046 --> 00:15:47.812
Where else would I be?

394
00:15:47.847 --> 00:15:50.130
I'm Empire's newest co-owner.

395
00:15:50.166 --> 00:15:51.349
(rising chatter)

396
00:15:51.384 --> 00:15:54.051
Hi.

397
00:15:58.891 --> 00:16:01.037
You own interest in Empire?
How the hell is that possible?

398
00:16:01.061 --> 00:16:04.978
Cookie gave me shares
in exchange for my son's heart.

399
00:16:05.014 --> 00:16:07.014
You traded Kingsley's heart?

400
00:16:07.050 --> 00:16:08.799
I saved your life. Andre.

401
00:16:10.737 --> 00:16:12.870
Close your mouth.
You're attracting flies.

402
00:16:12.905 --> 00:16:15.940
Why would you want
a part of Empire?

403
00:16:15.976 --> 00:16:18.309
I need a little fun in my life.

404
00:16:18.344 --> 00:16:20.778
I used to help Lucious
with his music back in the day.

405
00:16:20.814 --> 00:16:23.214
I was really good at it. too.
I had a real ear.

406
00:16:25.485 --> 00:16:27.852
And I want to be
close to my son.

407
00:16:29.672 --> 00:16:32.373
I-I... miss him so much.

408
00:16:38.164 --> 00:16:39.558
- Hey...
- (stammers)

409
00:16:39.582 --> 00:16:41.566
Can I hear my boy?

410
00:16:57.000 --> 00:17:00.551
Oh...
(exhales)

411
00:17:00.587 --> 00:17:03.153
There you are. my love.

412
00:17:03.189 --> 00:17:05.105
(cries)

413
00:17:06.776 --> 00:17:08.203
<i>COOKIE:
You got to make sure</i>

414
00:17:08.227 --> 00:17:09.688
you eat some of them
lamb chops. girl.

415
00:17:09.712 --> 00:17:12.213
That's iron.
That baby needs iron. now.

416
00:17:12.248 --> 00:17:13.675
Mmm. these green beans.
though. Mmm.

417
00:17:13.699 --> 00:17:15.182
Give that baby some meat. girl.

418
00:17:15.217 --> 00:17:18.002
No vegan grandchild...

419
00:17:18.037 --> 00:17:19.153
(laughs)

420
00:17:19.188 --> 00:17:20.605
(door opens)

421
00:17:20.640 --> 00:17:21.889
(door closes)

422
00:17:21.924 --> 00:17:23.218
ANDRE:
You gave White Tracy a stake

423
00:17:23.242 --> 00:17:25.192
in Empire?
Have you lost your mind?

424
00:17:25.227 --> 00:17:27.561
Have you lost your damn mind.
hollering at me?

425
00:17:29.148 --> 00:17:31.516
Dre. I would have given her
the whole damn company

426
00:17:31.551 --> 00:17:33.884
if that's what it would've taken
to save your life.

427
00:17:33.920 --> 00:17:36.454
(Cookie sighs)

428
00:17:36.489 --> 00:17:38.789
Now. she was supposed to let me
break the news to you.

429
00:17:38.824 --> 00:17:40.558
but I guess that goes to show

430
00:17:40.593 --> 00:17:42.454
you can't trust an ex-crackhead.

431
00:17:42.478 --> 00:17:43.805
So you just let her
into our boardroom.

432
00:17:43.829 --> 00:17:44.923
That's great. Ma.
That's real great.

433
00:17:44.947 --> 00:17:46.364
Does Pop know what you did?

434
00:17:46.399 --> 00:17:48.210
Oh. you think I need
your daddy's permission?

435
00:17:48.234 --> 00:17:50.601
(chuckles) Boy. you don't
know me at all. do you?

436
00:17:50.637 --> 00:17:52.119
TERI:
You know. Andre. you cannot

437
00:17:52.155 --> 00:17:54.254
be mad at Cookie
for trying to save your life.

438
00:17:54.290 --> 00:17:56.074
COOKIE:
Thank you. Teri. Glad somebody

439
00:17:56.109 --> 00:17:58.242
around here got
some good damn common sense.

440
00:17:58.277 --> 00:18:01.279
Oh. and I'm going with you
to your checkup tomorrow.

441
00:18:01.314 --> 00:18:04.181
Yeah. I need to make sure
my investment is paying off.

442
00:18:06.186 --> 00:18:09.603
Yeah. you better
sit your ass down.

443
00:18:11.808 --> 00:18:13.958
Well. I've been thinking...

444
00:18:13.993 --> 00:18:16.553
- Not a good time
to start that. Hakeem.
- Um. hello?

445
00:18:19.481 --> 00:18:22.450
I want to play Lucious
in the Empire movie.

446
00:18:22.485 --> 00:18:25.419
You know. I could bring
that realness. bro.

447
00:18:25.472 --> 00:18:27.088
Nobody can do that.

448
00:18:27.123 --> 00:18:30.123
We need a star in that role.
An A-list actor.

449
00:18:30.159 --> 00:18:32.660
COOKIE:
Well. now.
you can get a lot of press.

450
00:18:32.695 --> 00:18:34.461
a lot of hype.

451
00:18:34.496 --> 00:18:36.447
if Hakeem plays his daddy.

452
00:18:36.483 --> 00:18:38.082
(door opens)

453
00:18:38.117 --> 00:18:41.836
But I'm not sticking my nose
in Empire's business.

454
00:18:42.872 --> 00:18:44.771
Miss Maya is here.

455
00:18:44.807 --> 00:18:47.808
I keep telling her she doesn't
need to introduce me.

456
00:18:47.844 --> 00:18:49.126
Um. we have a problem.

457
00:18:49.161 --> 00:18:51.028
- What is it?
- MAYA: The feds

458
00:18:51.064 --> 00:18:52.491
just held a press conference
telling the world

459
00:18:52.515 --> 00:18:54.815
that Lucious
is a wanted fugitive.

460
00:18:54.850 --> 00:18:56.951
- Oh. that's great.
- (phone buzzing)

461
00:19:02.158 --> 00:19:03.774
Andre Lyon.

462
00:19:03.809 --> 00:19:05.510
Yes.

463
00:19:05.545 --> 00:19:07.128
I think that's shortsighted.

464
00:19:11.718 --> 00:19:13.895
Charlie Dupree is no longer
willing to play Lucious.

465
00:19:13.919 --> 00:19:17.004
and our co-financiers
are pulling out of the film.

466
00:19:17.039 --> 00:19:19.940
Yeah. 'cause they heard that
bitch press conference. right?

467
00:19:19.975 --> 00:19:22.143
Fox deal is gonna
come off the table next.

468
00:19:23.262 --> 00:19:25.379
The feds are trying
to destroy us.

469
00:19:35.324 --> 00:19:37.892
Look. when the hell
is this doctor gonna get here?

470
00:19:37.927 --> 00:19:39.826
He'll be here soon. Ma.

471
00:19:41.247 --> 00:19:45.032
Look. Andre. I know Empire
is on your mind. but...

472
00:19:45.067 --> 00:19:47.234
Pop trusted me with Empire. Ma.

473
00:19:47.270 --> 00:19:49.019
I can't let it fail.

474
00:19:49.055 --> 00:19:52.139
Boy. that thing will
work itself out. Okay?

475
00:19:52.175 --> 00:19:54.541
